This paper is about improving semantic parsing using neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a generator-reranker architecture, which involves training a critic network to rerank the candidates generated by the generator. This involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and improving the performance of the semantic parser, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
